<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="104" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">550 E 1/14</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Italian Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ricci</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-23"><hi rend="italic">January 23,
                                1922</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: By order of my Government I have
                            the honor to advise Your Excellency that the Italian Government has been
                            informed by the Russian Government that the Pan-Russian Executive
                            Committee has been called to meet on January 27 and elect the Russian
                            Delegation to the Genoa Conference vesting it with extraordinary full
                            powers.</p>
                        <p>The Russian Government has asked the Italian Government to bring the
                            foregoing to the knowledge of the Government of the United States of
                            America.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased to accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">V. Rolandi Ricci</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>